
// This Hyperlambda code sends a signal to a specific session using the [sockets.signal] slot. It constructs a message by concatenating strings and specifies the message type as "system". The signal is sent to the session identified by the value of the [session] node within the [.arguments] node. The [args] node contains the message details to be transmitted.
sockets.signal:x:@.arguments/*/session
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:system
